      <h1>Our Story</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="prose">
    <p class="lead">We are a family that never really stopped collecting. It started small, a mineral here, a fossil there, a coin passed down or picked up at a show.</p>
    <p>Over the years the shelves filled up with amethyst and fluorite, fish plates and shells, a wall of lava lamps, and a coin collection that grew quietly in the background. What began as a hobby turned into something we care about doing well.</p>
    <p>Grimsley Mineral Co. is our way of sharing that collection and everything we have learned keeping it. We are not a warehouse and we are not trying to be. We handle every piece ourselves, photograph it honestly, and tell you what we actually know about where it came from and what shape it is in. If we are not sure about something, we will say so.</p>
    <p>Our grand opening is at the Highway 127 Yard Sale, August 6 through 9, 2026. It is the largest yard sale in the country, and it felt like the right place to open our doors in person and meet the people who love this stuff as much as we do. After the 127, we move online only, so the shelves you see at the booth become the inventory you can browse from home.</p>
    <p>We are a new business, so we are not going to pretend we have decades of reviews or a fancy storefront. What we have is a real collection, an honest way of describing it, and a family that stands behind every piece we sell. Come see us at the 127, then find us online.</p>
    <p style="margin-top:30px;"><a class="btn btn-dark" href="/visit">See us at the 127</a></p>
  </div>
